message.content: A 42-year-old Caucasian male with no significant past medical history presents with fever, cough, and shortness of breath, and is diagnosed with COVID-19.
A 45-year-old Caucasian male with no significant past medical history presents with fever, cough, and shortness of breath, and has been recently exposed to a confirmed case of COVID-19.
A 65-year-old male, with a history of hypertension and diabetes, presents with fever, dry cough, and shortness of breath, and is later diagnosed with COVID-19.
A 68-year-old male of Asian descent with a history of hypertension presents with fever, cough, and shortness of breath, and is diagnosed with COVID-19.
